result.execSummary:
The defendant Francisca A Kadia was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • MA-Fraud/Benefit Application, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 49.49(1)(a)1.
  • MA-Fraud/Application for Benefits. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.
  • MA-Fraud/Application for Benefits. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Plea hearing proceeded. Defendant sworn in.

As to COUNTS 1-4 on the Amended Information:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgments of conviction entered.

COUNT 2- Medical Assistance Fraud (Forfeiture) , contrary to sec. 49.49(4m)(a)1, 49.49(4m)(b), Wis. Stats., a forfeiture.
